# Implementation Plan - Phase 12: Slide Section Changes

Redesign the slide preview interface to a more professional, "OpenSong-style" layout. This includes a high-density list of slides with metadata and automatic blank slide generation.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The shortcut detection (C for Chorus, V for Verse, etc.) will rely on parsing the lyrics. If no tags like `[Chorus]` or `Chorus:` are found, it will default to sequential verse numbering (V1, V2, etc.). Does this match your expectation?

> [!NOTE]
> Blank slides will be appended to the end of the song's slide list. When selected, they will project a completely blank screen (Black), effectively clearing both lyrics and title.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Data & Logic

#### [NEW] `lib/features/live_controller/domain/slide.dart`
Define a `Slide` model to hold metadata for each projection unit.
- `title`: The song title or Bible reference.
- `shortcut`: Short tag like 'C', 'V1', 'B'.
- `content`: The full text to be projected.
- `isBlank`: Flag for blank slides.

#### [NEW] `lib/features/live_controller/presentation/slide_utils.dart`
Helper functions to parse lyrics into `Slide` objects.
- Regex-based detection of stanza types.
- Logic to add blank slides at the end of a list.

### UI Components

#### [NEW] `lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/slide_item_widget.dart`
A premium, low-height list item for slides.
- **Section 1**: Title/Ref (Grey, small font).
- **Section 2**: Shortcut tag in a small box or highlighted (e.g., `[C]`).
- **Section 3**: First line of content (Truncated with ellipsis).
- Hover and Active states with vibrant accents (Blue/Purple).

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/preview_pane.dart`
- Use the new parsing logic to generate a list of `Slide` objects from the selected song.
- Replace the old `Card` items with `SlideItemWidget`.
- Ensure the blank slide is selectable and functional.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Unit tests for `SlideUtils` to ensure various lyrics formats are parsed correctly.
- Verify that "Blank" slides are correctly inserted.

### Manual Verification
1. Open KeryxPro and select a song (e.g., "Amazing Grace").
2. Verify the slides appear in the new 3-part format.
3. Check that the shortcut column shows 'V1', 'V2', etc. (or 'C' if tags are added).
4. Scroll to the bottom and verify a blank slide exists.
5. Click the blank slide and verify the "Monitor" shows a blank screen/background.
6. Verify that long lines in the preview section are correctly truncated with "...".
